# Local runtime recovery

When `next dev` shows 500, blank `/_next/static`, or port conflicts:

1. Run `node scripts/msc-kill-dev-port.mjs` (or `MSC_DEV_PORT`) — never guess PIDs.
2. Optional one-shot: `node scripts/msc-dev-recover.mjs` with `MSC_DEV_RECOVER_CLEAN=1`.
3. Safe build prep: `node scripts/msc-verify-next-safe.mjs` — never `clean:next` while dev listens on `MSC_DEV_PORT` (default 3000).
4. HTTP smoke after dev is up: `node scripts/msc-local-http-smoke.mjs`.

Cursor hook `.cursor/hooks/msc-guard-clean-while-dev.mjs` blocks destructive cache wipes during live dev when `hooks.json` is enabled.

SQLite: backup before repair (`scripts/msc-sqlite-repair.mjs`), WAL purge before deploy (`scripts/msc-sqlite-wal-purge.mjs`). See `.cursor/docs/sqlite-repair-manifest.md`.
